Third-party tools and services
------------------------------

Video Automation can call optional third-party command-line tools and services
when configured by the user. These tools are not owned by this project and may
be governed by their own licenses, terms of service, and usage policies.

Common optional tools and services include:

- FFmpeg / FFprobe for media probing, decoding, and rendering.
- yt-dlp if users choose to install or use it outside the current default UI.
- faster-whisper, FunASR, Demucs, Pillow, and other optional Python packages.
- OpenAI-compatible APIs, OpenRouter, and Google Gemini APIs for optional AI
  cover, metadata, highlight, or subtitle translation features.
- Inter and JetBrains Mono web fonts, whose license files are kept under
  web/fonts/.

Users are responsible for ensuring they have the rights to process, record,
transcribe, translate, publish, or redistribute any media they provide to the
software.
